name: Matthew Sluka
summary: Matthew Sluka, the starting quarterback for the undefeated UNLV football team, has left the program over a dispute related to NIL (name, image, and likeness) compensation. According to reports, Sluka claims that he was promised a certain amount of NIL money but did not receive it. The situation has sparked a discussion about the growing role of NIL in college football and the tensions it can create between players and universities. UNLV has issued a statement saying that they are "disappointed" by Sluka's decision and that they "will continue to work towards providing our student-athletes with the best possible experience." Sluka's departure comes at a crucial time for UNLV, as the team is currently 6-0 and has aspirations of making the College Football Playoff.

name: Julie Chrisley resentencing
summary: Julie Chrisley, the star of the reality TV show "Chrisley Knows Best," has been resentenced to serve 84 months in prison for bank fraud and tax evasion. The sentence was upheld by the court, despite an emotional plea from Chrisley during her court appearance. After being released from federal custody ahead of her resentencing, Chrisley has now been given a revised sentence of seven years. The decision was made following an earlier resentencing hearing, and Chrisley has since apologized for her actions. Her daughter, Savannah Chrisley, has expressed fear ahead of her mother's imprisonment.

name: Cat Glover
summary: Cat Glover, a celebrated singer, dancer, and choreographer, has passed away at the age of 60. She was renowned for her collaborations with iconic musician Prince, particularly during his "Sign O' the Times" and "Lovesexy" eras. Glover's dynamic stage presence and captivating dance moves left a lasting impression, enhancing Prince's performances and solidifying her status as a Prince protégée. Her talent and impact on the music industry are widely acknowledged, as evidenced by the tributes and remembrances from entertainment publications and Prince's fans.

name: Monster Hunter Wilds
summary: Capcom has announced that Monster Hunter Wilds is set to launch on February 28, 2025. The title will be available on PlayStation and will introduce a new flagship monster named Arkveld. Along with the release date announcement, Capcom also unveiled a story trailer showcasing new gameplay footage and revealed pre-order bonuses. Pre-orders for the physical edition of the game, including a Steelbook Edition, are now available. Despite the excitement surrounding the release date announcement, the news has raised concerns among some modders who are worried about the game's "uncanny talking Palicos" and whether they will have enough time to silence them before the game's launch.

name: Brett Favre
summary: Retired NFL legend Brett Favre has publicly disclosed his diagnosis of Parkinson's disease. The NFL Hall of Famer revealed his condition during a House hearing on welfare funds. According to Favre, he received his diagnosis in January after experiencing issues with his right arm. Parkinson's disease is a neurodegenerative disorder that affects movement, balance, and coordination. Favre expressed gratitude for the support of his family and faith, while acknowledging the challenges ahead. His diagnosis has shed light on the impact of Parkinson's disease, emphasizing its prevalence and the importance of early detection and management.
